ied paypal payment and using the transaction with the &quot;accused&quot; legally access the verified paypal information on the accused that is available to people who have transactions.  This could have been as simple as an email address with a first name last name.  Then go to a site like dejanews and find any posts made by that email address that the accused signed with his real name, or find any email addresses linked to the real name found from paypal.  Correlate the names/email addresses via a white pages lookup.  Also visit any of the accused's public website that could have come with any of the ISP account linked to any email addresses found to get the published pictures, or any other leades that the accused may have posted in newsgroups.  That is the simplest way that I would go about getting the information if it I was going to do it.  If the &quot;hacker&quot; was an admin of the guild's message board, the IP address that the accused used to post his brag message is something he can freely and legally access and could be used via reverse DNS lookup to confirm that the poster's ISP and compare with the ISP of anyone who posted on a newsgroup with the same first name last name email account combination.<br><br>The only bit of released information that I'm not sure about legality wise is the acne perscription.  He could have gotten it from the perscription database that the RX uses before dispensing perscriptions, insurance information, medical records, credit card payment, etc.  The only legal ways the &quot;hacker&quot; could have found it out would be if after getting the name/address he found someone who knew the accused and got the info, he visited the accused and saw the accused using the perscripton in a public place, or he &quot;dumpster dived&quot; the accused trash.<br><br>There are even more way to get the info if he was willing to break or bend any laws, but there are lots of legal ways that are not that hard to do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><